## Core Features

### Feature 1: Directions Endpoint URL Construction

**As a developer**, I want to construct routing request URLs from origin and destination inputs, so I can build correctly encoded routing URLs for addresses and coordinates.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a JSON command with `endpoint` set to `directions`, an API key, and `origin` and `destination` values. Each endpoint value may be either a string address or an object with numeric `lat` and `lng` fields. The output is exactly one line, `url=<full URL>`, when both endpoints are valid. Address strings are percent-encoded in query parameters, coordinate objects render as `lat,lng`, and invalid endpoint values render a neutral validation error identifying the failing field and the expected category.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature1_directions_endpoints.json`

```json
{
    "description": "Build a directions request URL from origin and destination inputs, accepting either textual addresses or latitude/longitude coordinates and rejecting unsupported endpoint values.",
    "cases": [
        {
            "input": {
                "api_key": "MY_API_KEY",
                "endpoint": "directions",
                "origin": "Paris, France",
                "destination": "Marseilles, France"
            },
            "expected_output": "url=https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json?origin=Paris%2C%20France&destination=Marseilles%2C%20France&key=MY_API_KEY\n"
        },
        {
            "input": {
                "api_key": "MY_API_KEY",
                "endpoint": "directions",
                "origin": {
                    "lat": 23.43,
                    "lng": 65.1
                },
                "destination": {
                    "lat": 62.323,
                    "lng": 53.1
                }
            },
            "expected_output": "url=https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json?origin=23.43,65.1&destination=62.323,53.1&key=MY_API_KEY\n"
        }
    ]
}
```

