### Feature 4: Geocoding URL Construction

**As a developer**, I want to construct geocoding request URLs, so I can look up addresses, coordinates, or place identifiers through a consistent adapter.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a JSON command with `endpoint` set to `geocoding`, an API key, and one of the supported lookup inputs: `address`, `location`, or `place_id`. Optional `bounds`, `language`, `region`, and `components` fields add query constraints. The output is exactly one `url=<full URL>` line. Address text and component values are percent-encoded where required, bounds render as two coordinate corners separated by `|`, and coordinates render as `lat,lng`.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature4_geocoding_urls.json`

```json
{
    "description": "Build a geocoding request URL for address lookup, coordinate lookup, place identifier lookup, bounds, language, region, and component filters.",
    "cases": [
        {
            "input": {
                "api_key": "MY_API_KEY",
                "endpoint": "geocoding",
                "address": "1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA"
            },
            "expected_output": "url=https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=1600%20Amphitheatre%20Parkway%2C%20Mountain%20View%2C%20CA&key=MY_API_KEY\n"
        },
        {
            "input": {
                "api_key": "MY_API_KEY",
                "endpoint": "geocoding",
                "address": "Winnetka",
                "bounds": {
                    "northeast": {
                        "lat": 34.172684,
                        "lng": -118.604794
                    },
                    "southwest": {
                        "lat": 34.236144,
                        "lng": -118.500938
                    }
                }
            },
            "expected_output": "url=https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=Winnetka&bounds=34.172684,-118.604794|34.236144,-118.500938&key=MY_API_KEY\n"
        }
    ]
}
```

