### Feature 11: Time Zone and Geolocation URL Construction

**As a developer**, I want to construct time and geolocation request URLs, so I can call the correct service host and path for temporal and device-location lookup requests.

**Expected Behavior / Usage:**

The input is a JSON command with either `endpoint` set to `timezone` or `geolocation`. Time zone input includes an API key, coordinate `location`, Unix-second `timestamp`, and optional `language`, and outputs a URL using the maps time zone path. Geolocation input includes an API key and outputs a URL using the distinct geolocation service host and path. In both cases the output is exactly one `url=<full URL>` line.

**Test Cases:** `rcb_tests/public_test_cases/feature11_time_and_geolocation_urls.json`

```json
